INSERT INTO `country_hero_section` VALUES (1,_binary '\0','string',1,1),(2,_binary '\0','desc',2,1363),(3,_binary '\0','Egypt is a captivating country located in the northeastern corner of Africa, with its territory spanning into the Middle East, as the Sinai Peninsula connects it to Asia. Renowned for its ancient civilization, Egypt is steeped in history, culture, and iconic landmarks.',4,1396),(4,_binary '\0','Antigua and Barbuda is a sovereign island country in the Caribbean, located at the intersection of the Caribbean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean in the Leeward Islands part of the Lesser Antilles. It consists of two major islands, Antigua and Barbuda, and several smaller islands, including Great Bird, Green, Guiana, Long, Maiden, Prickly Pear, York, and Redonda. St. John\'s is the country\'s capital, major city, and largest port, while Codrington is Barbuda\'s largest town. \nMost people are of African descent, and English is the main language spoken. The majority of the population lives in Antigua, with most inhabitants living in St. Johns. \nThe backbone of the nation\'s economy lies in tourism, with an expanding offshore banking sector supplementing its growth. ',5,1985),(5,_binary '\0','Dominica is an island country located in the Lesser Antilles of the Caribbean Sea. It is situated between the French islands of Guadeloupe and Martinique. Its capital is Roseau. The majority of its population has African or mixed African-European heritage, with English as the official language and French patois also spoken. Dominica\'s economy heavily relies on agriculture, particularly banana cultivation, and has been working on developing its tourism industry. The island is rich in forests and biodiversity, home to a variety of birds and animals. It is known for its natural beauty, lush flora, and fauna, attracting nature enthusiasts and eco-tourists alike.',6,1993),(6,_binary '\0','Saint Kitts and Nevis, a captivating duo of islands nestled in the heart of the Caribbean, have a special charm despite its small size. St Kitts is the larger island, located to the northwest, while Nevis, the smaller island, is situated to the southeast of St Kitts, separated by a narrow channel known as \"The Narrows\". \nThe people of Saint Kitts and Nevis, predominantly of African descent, embody a warm and welcoming spirit that is reflected in their vibrant culture. English is the official language, and Christianity is the predominant religion, shaping the customs, festivals, and way of life on the islands. \nSaint Kitts and Nevis offer a diverse range of experiences that cater to every visitor\'s desires.',7,2001),(7,_binary '\0','Nestled in the southeastern Caribbean Sea, Grenada, known as the \"Spice Isle,\" is a picturesque gem offering a captivating blend of natural beauty, rich cultural heritage, and warm hospitality. The country consists of three main islands: Grenada, Carriacou, and Petit Martinique. Grenada\'s capital, St. George\'s, is known for its pastel-coloured houses, yachting and charter-boat centre, and fine natural harbour. \nThe population of Grenada is characterized by its diverse cultural makeup, influenced by African, European, and indigenous Carib ancestry. The official language is English, and the major religious groups are Christianity (mostly Roman Catholic and Protestant) and Rastafarianism.',8,2009),(8,_binary '\0','Malta is an island country in southern Europe, located in the Mediterranean Sea. It\'s a tiny archipelago, consisting of three main islands: Malta, Gozo, and Comino, along with some smaller islets, situated just south of Sicily and north of Africa. is a popular tourist destination, known for its warm climate, beautiful beaches, and rich history. The country has a long and fascinating past, having been ruled by various civilizations over the centuries, including the Phoenicians, Romans, Arabs, Normans, and British. This rich history is reflected in Malta\'s architecture, culture, and cuisine. \nMalta is a densely populated country, making it the tenth-smallest country by area in the world, but also the fifth most densely populated!',9,2035),(9,_binary '\0','Portugal is a southwestern European country on the Iberian Peninsula. It is known for its rich history, beautiful beaches, and delicious food. Bordered by Spain to the east and north and bounded by the Atlantic Ocean to the west and south,the country boasts a diverse coastline that stretches for over 800 kilometers (about 500 miles). This coastal position has historically influenced Portugal\'s identity as a maritime nation, shaping its culture, cuisine, and exploration endeavors.\nLively cities like Lisbon and Porto showcase Portugal\'s cultural heritage. Lisbon boasts historical sites like the So Jorge Castle and the Jernimos Monastery. Porto, famous for its Port wine production, has a charming medieval Ribeira district.',10,2221),(10,_binary '\0','Spain occupies a prime location in southwestern Europe. The majority of the country lies on the Iberian Peninsula, a large landmass jutting out into the Atlantic Ocean. Bordered by Portugal to the west, and by France and Andorra to the north, its geographical boundaries are defined by the imposing Pyrenees mountain range, separating Spain from mainland Europe. Spain\'s cityscapes are bursting with personality, offering a range for every traveler\'s taste. Madrid, the capital, throbs with cultural energy, housing world-class museums and a nightlife scene that lasts well into the morning. Barcelona, Catalonia\'s heart, boasts Gaud\'s architectural marvels like the Sagrada Familia, while Seville in Andalusia tempts visitors with flamenco shows and tapas-lined streets.',11,2248),(11,_binary '\0','The United Arab Emirates sits in the southeast corner of the Arabian Peninsula. Wedged between Oman to the east and Saudi Arabia on its other sides, the UAE boasts shorelines on the Persian Gulf. This location, where Europe, Asia, and Africa meet, makes the UAE a key center for trade.\nThe UAE isn\'t one big country, but rather a union of seven smaller ones called emirates. These emirates are all ruled by a group of leaders, with Abu Dhabi, the biggest emirate, acting as the capital. The other emirates are Dubai, Sharjah, Ajman, Umm Al-Quwain, Fujairah, and Ras Al Khaimah.\nThe UAE is famous for its modern cities, fancy hotels, and booming economy. Oil and gas were the big moneymakers for a long time, but the UAE has been working hard to not rely on just those resources. Dubai and Abu Dhabi are especially well-known for attracting businesses and tourists from all over the world, with their impressive skyscrapers, luxurious places to stay, and exciting cultural offerings.',12,2256),(12,_binary '\0','The Hellenic Republic, or Greece, occupies a strategic position in southeastern Europe, where the continents of Europe, Asia, and Africa converge. As the southernmost tip of the Balkan Peninsula, Greece boasts a dramatic coastline bordering the Aegean Sea to the east, the Ionian Sea to the west, and the Mediterranean Sea to the south. Its neighbors include Albania, North Macedonia, Bulgaria, and Turkey. \nGreece\'s landscape is a captivating tapestry. Mountainous regions rise majestically, while picturesque coastlines and a multitude of islands, scattered across the Aegean and Ionian Seas, create a breathtaking panorama. The mainland is dominated by mountain ranges, including the legendary Mount Olympus, once believed to be the home of the Greek gods. Stunning beaches grace the coastline, while the islands offer unique experiences, from the volcanic majesty of Santorini to the verdant landscapes of Corfu.\nAthens, the vibrant capital and largest city, is a treasure trove of ancient wonders, including the Acropolis, Parthenon, and Temple of Olympian Zeus. Thessaloniki, Patras, and Heraklion are other notable cities, each with its own distinct character.',13,2264),(13,_binary '\0','Encompassing a breathtaking tapestry of landscapes, the nation transitions from the Rocky Mountains\' soaring peaks to the fertile plains of the Midwest, and from the verdant forests of the Pacific Northwest to the sun-kissed beaches of California and Florida. This rich tapestry extends beyond geography.  The USA boasts 50 distinct states, each contributing its unique cultural thread to the national fabric.\nWith Washington, D.C. serving as its federal capital, the USA stands as a constitutional republic and a powerhouse on the global stage. Renowned for its economic strength, cultural dynamism, and significant influence in international affairs, the United States continues to shape the course of the 21st century.',14,2289),(14,_binary '\0','Saint Lucia, a sovereign state nestled in the eastern Caribbean Sea, is a member of the Lesser Antilles archipelago. Its strategic placement along eastern Caribbean sea lanes has made it a significant crossroads for trade and naval activity throughout history. The capital, Castries, situated on the northwestern coast, serves as the island\'s economic and cultural hub. Other notable towns include Gros Islet, Soufrire, and Vieux Fort. \nSaint Lucia\'s allure lies in its compact size, breathtaking volcanic peaks, and lush tropical environment. Its strategic position has significantly influenced its ',15,2303),(15,_binary '\0','Cyprus, officially known as the Republic of Cyprus, is an island nation situated in the eastern Mediterranean Sea. Although geographically part of Western Asia, it is culturally and politically aligned with Southeast Europe. Cyprus ranks as the third-largest and third-most populous island in the Mediterranean. Neighboring countries include Greece to the east, Egypt to the south, Turkey to the north, and Lebanon and Syria to the west. The capital and largest city of Cyprus is Nicosia.\nToday, Cyprus is known for its diverse cultural heritage, stunning landscapes, and significant archaeological sites. ',16,2356),(16,_binary '\0','Austria, officially known as the Republic of Austria, is a country surrounded by land in the middle of Europe. It borders eight other countries: Germany to the northwest, the Czech Republic to the north, Slovakia to the northeast, Hungary to the east, Slovenia to the south, Italy to the southwest, and Switzerland and Liechtenstein to the west. Austria is famous for its mountains, the Alps, which take up most of the country. This makes it a great place for skiing and climbing. A big river, the Danube, also runs through Austria. Vienna, the capital city, is known for its history, old buildings, and art. Because of where it is and its long history as part of a big empire, Austria has played an important role in European politics.',17,2371);
