INSERT INTO `process_time` VALUES (9,_binary '\0','Antigua and Barbuda\'s Citizenship by Investment Program has reasonable documentation, straightforward procedures, and post-approval virtual interviews for main applicants and dependents aged 16 and older. Passport collection in Antigua and Barbuda follows, with an estimated three to four months processing time, barring any concerns with the application.',23),(10,_binary '\0','The processing time for the Dominica Citizenship by Investment program is typically 3 to 6 months, with the standard processing time being 3 to 4 months. Upon approval, the applicant must fulfill the investment condition by contributing to the state fund or purchasing government-approved real estate.The entire procedure is entirely remote, and investors are not required to visit the country before or after obtaining citizenship.',24),(11,_binary '\0','The Egypt Citizenship Investment application typically takes 6 to 12 months for processing. Factors influencing the timeframe include document completeness, application volume, and government efficiency. Applicants are advised to submit accurate documentation promptly to avoid delays. It\'s recommended to stay informed about the application status and respond promptly to any requests.',25),(12,_binary '\0','The St. Kitts and Nevis citizenship by investment program usually takes about four months to finish. It\'s known for being quick and straightforward. This short time frame shows the program\'s dedication to making it easy for people who want citizenship through investing in St. Kitts and Nevis.',26),(13,_binary '\0','The St. Lucia citizenship by investment program usually takes about four months to finish. It\'s known for being quick and straightforward. You will get citizenship and passport approved by the St. Lucia Government within that time frame. Mandatory interviews required for applicants and family members.',27),(14,_binary '\0','The application process for Grenada citizenship by investment is straightforward and efficient. The applicant is not required to visit Grenada beforehand, the application can be done remotely. The process takes about five to six months as the approval for citizenship and a passport is obtained within this timeframe.',28),(15,_binary '\0','The processing time for obtaining Malta Citizenship through investment varies based on the applicant\'s situation. If the applicant already holds Maltese residency, the minimum duration for citizenship is 12 months. The processing time for obtaining Maltese citizenship through investment typically spans from 12 to 36 months.',29),(16,_binary '\0','The estimated time frame for obtaining citizenship takes around 24 to 36 months. Successful applicants receive full citizenship of the Republic of Austria by decision of the Government of Austria and can apply for a passport straight away. Passports are issued within a few days.',30),(17,_binary '\0','The entire procedure of the Portugal Golden Visa application typically takes around eight to ten months. The application and the required documents are submitted online. Once the application is approved, the applicant need to appear for an interview in person, in the Portuguese Immigration Office.',31),(18,_binary '\0','The entire procedure of the Spain Golden Visa application typically takes around five months, which includes Due Diligence, preparing documents and application. Though the process of the application takes only 20 days.',32),(19,_binary '\0','The Greece Golden Visa typically takes 3 to 4 months to process, including Due Diligence, preparing documents and application. The exact timeline may vary depending on various factors.',33),(20,_binary '\0','To apply for the UAE Golden Visa, investors need to first obtain the entry permit, which can take 2-7 working days if all their documents are correct. Once they have the entry permit, they can proceed with the Golden Visa application, which may take up to 30 days to process.',34),(21,_binary '\0','The fast-track Cyprus residency by investment program allows individuals to obtain residency in approximately two months, providing a quick and efficient pathway for those seeking to relocate.',35),(22,_binary '\0','The processing time for EB-5 visas isn\'t quick and can take a while. Typically, getting conditional permanent resident status takes about two years and removing the conditions requires another two years. Applicants might need to wait for up to three years.',36);
